The United States is showing support for the Cuban people who have taken to the streets to protest against the communist regime. President Biden has directed measures to support the Cuban people and hold the Cuban regime accountable. The U.S. Department of the Treasury has sanctioned a Cuban individual and entity for human rights abuses. The administration is engaging with the international community to condemn the violence and repression in Cuba. Efforts are being made to ensure that Cuban citizens have access to the internet and information. The administration is listening to Cuban American leaders and seeking their recommendations. The policy on remittances is being reviewed to ensure funds reach the Cuban people. The U.S. Embassy in Havana is being restaffed to enhance consular services and support for the Cuban people.